Annual Meeting of DPRK Olympic Committee Held  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- An annual meeting of the Olympic Committee of the DPRK was held at the People's Palace of Culture on Mar. 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting reviewed the work of the committee in Juche 95 (2006) and discussed the action program for Juche 96 (2007). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report was made by Mun Jae Dok, chairman of the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission of the DPRK who is chairman of the DPRK Olympic Committee, to be followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers noted that the committee had conducted its work as required by the idea of the Olympic movement in the past period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They set forth tasks and ways to successfully ensure the qualifying tournaments for the Beijing Olympics in 2008 by enhancing the functions and roles of the DPRK Olympic Committee and associations of sport events. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting informed the participants of materials on the work with international sports organizations.

U.S.-S. Korea Joint Military Games Assailed  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- The Friendship Association with Korea based in Spain and the Arab Solidarity Committee for Supporting the Struggle of the Anti-imperialist National Democratic Front and the south Korean People issued statements on Mar. 16 in denunciation of the projected U.S.-south Korea RSOI and Foal Eagle joint military drills. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is utterly intolerable that the U.S. and the south Korean authorities are engaged in aggressive war maneuvers threatening the peace and stability of the Korean Peninsula and Northeast Asia at a time when not only the Korean people but also the world peace-loving people are heaping bitter curses on the U.S. occupation of south Korea and its monstrous acts, the statements said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They predicted that the hostile acts of the United States were fated to fiasco in face of the might of the army and people of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the meantime, the U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics made public a statement on Mar. 18 urging the U.S. and the south Korean authorities to immediately give up the planned war exercises threatening peace in Asia and the rest of the world.

U.S. Forces of Aggression Busy with Preparations for Joint Military Exercises  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- The United States is pushing the situation on the Korean Peninsula to a new pitch of tension by deploying its forces of aggression in south Korea for RSOI and Foal Eagle joint war maneuvers to be staged in south Korea and in its vicinity, according to a military source. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialist forces of aggression transferred one wing of Stealth fighter-bomber F-117, the main player of the air force in the war exercises, and at least 300 troops to south Korea from the U.S. mainland in January and deployed overseas-based F-15, F/A-18 and E-2C in south Korea in March. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those U.S. mainland-and overseas-based warplanes are now engaged in madcap navigation exercises and drills for striking ground targets almost every day. They are also busy with air battle exercises targeted against the DPRK in cooperation with the U.S. 7th Air Force in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 25th Infantry Division of the 1st Corps of the U.S. imperialist forces of aggression has recently been transferred to south Korea from its mainland. And they, at the same time, massively introduced there the latest war hardware to be used in the above-said war maneuvers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Timed to coincide with these moves, south Korean military ports are crowded with a U.S. landing craft with a U.S. marine expeditionary group aboard, a dock landing craft, a dock landing transport ship and "Blue Ridge," a flag ship of the 7th Fleet of the U.S. imperialist forces of aggression, and vehicle transport ships. Meanwhile, the task force of nuclear-powered super- large carrier "Ronald Reagan" is busy with its maneuver in the waters off the southern coast of Pusan to create a war atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In another development, 12 "F-22A" (raptor) Stealth fighter-bombers and over 250 troops deployed in the air force base of the U.S. imperialist forces of aggression in Kadena, Okinawa, from the U.S. mainland in February are ready to participate in the war exercises and Guam-based B-52s are also ready to go into action.

Rodong Sinmun on Keeping Tight Hold on Baton of Revolution 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Friday dedicates an editorial to the 90th anniversary of the Korean National Association formed by indomitable revolutionary fighter Kim Hyong Jik. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the formation of the KNA by Kim Hyong Jik on March 23, Juche 6 (1917) was a historic event which paved the way for a radical turn in the development of the anti-Japanese national liberation movement in Korea, the editorial says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of great leadership which began with the idea of "Aim high" and has been given continuity pure and clean through generations is now being steadily carried forward by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has devoted his all to the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered in Mt. Paektu with a noble sense of obligation to the times and revolution, the country and the people. The Korean people owe it to him that they have become to display the honor of a revolutionary people living and struggling in Kim Hyong Jik's idea of "Aim high" through generations and that this land has greeted the new history of the building of a great prosperous powerful nation in which the ideal and desire of the revolutionary forerunners are being brought to overall realization under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean revolution led by Kim Jong Il is the one strong in Juche character in which the idea of national independence is being materialized to the fullest measure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The banner of national independence upheld by Kim Hyong Jik who walked the untrodden path of the Korean revolution at its dawn is flying as always under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean revolution led by Kim Jong Il is the one with a vast prospect which wins one victory after another with the might of revolutionary comradeship and the might of single-minded unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyong Jik created a noble history of revolutionary comradeship in the course of the arduous struggle for embodying the idea of "Aim high" after setting it forth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tradition of comradeship of the Korean revolution is lofty in its origin and its continuity is firmly guaranteed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean revolution led by Kim Jong Il is an invincible one which emerges victorious in indomitable fighting spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyong Jik said in the early days of his activity that a revolutionary must be prepared for death from hunger, death from beating and death from cold. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans are a heroic people fighting with the indomitable faith planted in their minds by Kim Jong Il. In this spirit did they change the "Arduous March" into a cheerful march and open a broad avenue for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation, overcoming a thousand and one trials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the greatest honor of the Korean people to vigorously push forward the revolution and construction generation after generation with a tight hold on the baton of the revolution, blessed with illustrious leaders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of the continuity of the Korean revolution should be glorified through generations in single-mindedly upholding Kim Jong Il's Songun policy and devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution.

Struggle against U.S. and War and GNP Called for in S. Korea  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- South Korean youth and students organizations reportedly released statements on Mar. 18, 25 years since the arson on the "American Cultural Service" in Pusan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils in its statement said that the arson on the above-said service on Mar. 18, 1982 was a brave struggle of youth and students as it disclosed the aggressive nature and colors of the U.S. as a colonial ruler and called upon all the patriotic people to turn out in the movement against the U.S. and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Calling on the youth and students to wage a struggle to frustrate the U.S. desperate moves to block the national reunification, impose the disaster of war upon the Korean nation and thus dominate the whole Korean Peninsula, the statement said that this is the way of inheriting the spirit displayed by the participants in the arson. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Youth and Students Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration in its statement said that the anti-U.S. struggle has become a trend in the June 15 era of reunification and the Korean nation is bringing about a heyday of independent reunification through its concerted efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that those forerunners set fire to the "American Cultural Service" 25 years ago to let the people know about the aggressive nature and the true colors of the U.S., the statement appealed to the members of the solidarity to encourage their schoolmates and people to launch actions against the U.S. and war for the withdrawal of the U.S. troops and against the Grand National Party of south Korea.

Rodong Sinmun Demands Halt to Projected Joint Military Maneuvers 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- The U.S. and south Korean authorities should unconditionally cancel their planned reckless joint military maneuvers against the DPRK if they truly hail the trend of reconciliation on the Korean Peninsula and expect its smooth development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-targeted joint military exercises staged by the U.S. and south Korean bellicose forces in south Korea every year have been a main factor of threatening the peace on the Korean Peninsula and escalating the confrontation and tension on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is impossible to terminate the military confrontation, defuse tension and eliminate the danger of war from the Korean Peninsula unless those DPRK-targeted joint military exercises are brought to an end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and south Korean bellicose forces' projected RSOI and Foal Eagle are typical anti-DPRK saber-rattling. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These war maneuvers will involve tens of thousands of the U.S. imperialist aggression troops and ultra-modern war hardware including a nuclear powered carrier and Stealth fighter-bombers that earned an ill-fame in battle fields of war of aggression in Iraq and various other parts of the world. These war exercises will be expected to be of more provocative nature than any previous ones as main emphasis will be put on offensive exercises including landing, river-crossing and striking targets in the depth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. and south Korean bellicose forces stage such provocative large-scale joint military maneuvers, they will saliently reveal their hostility towards the DPRK and attempt to invade it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dialogue and war exercises can never go together. It is hard to expect any success at a dialogue under the situation where people are disturbed by gunfire during DPRK-targeted war maneuvers. This is clearly evidenced by what they experienced in the past. The projected reckless anti-DPRK joint military exercises would only result in disturbing the peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula, driving again the inter-Korean relations to a crisis and fanning up the atmosphere of war.

Wreaths Laid before Statues and Grave of Kim Hyong Jik 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the Statue of Kim Hyong Jik, an indomitable revolutionary fighter and outstanding leader of the anti-Japanese national liberation movement in Korea, in Ponghwa-ri and his grave in Mangyongdae on March 23 on the occasion of the 90th anniversary of the Korean National Association led by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen before his statue and grave were wreaths sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremonies were senior officials of the party, the army and the state, the chairperson of a friendly party, officials of the party and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and working people and school youth and children in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also placed there were wreaths in the name of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Laid there were wreaths in the name of working people's organizations, ministries, national institutions, and scientific, educational, culture and art, pubic health and media institutions, the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School and party and power organs, factories, farms and schools in Pyongyang and bouquets and flowers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants observed a moment's silence in memory of the noble revolutionary life of Kim Hyong Jik. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day wreaths, bouquets and flowers were placed before his statues at Kim Hyong Jik Military Medical University and in Sakju County of North Phyongan Province and Junggang County of Jagang Province.

World Meteorological Day Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- The World Meteorological Organization (WMO) chose the theme dealing with the issues pending an urgent solution for the existence and activities of human beings and social development in the field of meteorology and the issues, which require much effort, on World Meteorological Day every year and directed main efforts to its implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson today says this in a signed article dedicated to the day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the theme for the year 2007 is "Polar Meteorology: Understanding Global Impacts," the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WMO has made much effort to observe the climatic and environmental changes in the poles and thus prevent the global damage caused by them in close touch with the national meteorological and hydrological services. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A unified and well-organized management system for the meteorological field has been established in the DPRK under the deep concern of the state. The DPRK, as a member state of the WMO, will strengthen the international cooperation with other countries and meteorological organizations to make positive contributions to preventing the damage caused by abnormal climatic phenomena including natural disasters on the global scale in the future, too.

KNA, Pioneer of National Independence and Unity
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- Ninety years have passed since the Korean National Association was formed by Kim Hyong Jik, an indomitable revolutionary fighter and an outstanding leader of the anti-Japanese national liberation movement of Korea (March 23). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-Japanese movement of the Korean people was split and doomed to bitter failure owing to the splitting acts and flunkeyism of nationalists in the 1910s when the destiny of the country was at stake after the occupation of Korea by the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyong Jik, basing himself in a deep analysis of the situation, unfolded a far-reaching plan to form a revolutionary organization based on the internal force of the nation with transparent anti-imperialist, independent stand and popular among the people in order to destroy the fascist and repressive politics of the Japanese imperialists and achieve the independence of Korea.  And he energetically pushed ahead with its preparation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Basing himself on the preparations, he formed the Korean National Association, an anti-Japanese underground revolutionary organization, in Pyongyang on March 23, Juche 6 (1917). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KNA was a secret organization with the aim of achieving national independence and establishing a truly civilized country through the concerted efforts of the Korean nation.  It was the largest anti-Japanese underground revolutionary organization of Korean patriots at home and abroad around the March First Popular Uprising. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With the formation of the KNA with the most transparent independent stand against imperialism the anti-Japanese national liberation movement in Korea came to have the pivotal organization to rally broad segments of the people with a correct purpose of struggle and a new phase was opened up for achieving the unity of the anti-Japanese revolutionary forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the guidance of Kim Hyong Jik the KNA waged various forms of struggle including the revolutionary armed activities and united broad sections of the people to vigorously arouse them to the anti-Japanese struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KNA made a great contribution to developing the anti-Japanese national liberation movement in Korea to a proletarian revolution from the nationalist movement and achieving the unity for the anti-Japanese independence movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal exploits Kim Hyong Jik performed to make a history of national independence and unity at the dawn of the Korean revolution were carried forward by President Kim Il Sung and have been carried into a brilliant reality by Kim Jong Il who has the idea of loving the country, nation and people on the highest level.

Polar Meteorological Research in DPRK Intensified
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- March 23 is World Meteorological Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion of the day, Director of the Central Meteorological Institute of the DPRK Ryu Ki Ryol gave the following answers to the questions put by KCNA as regards the polar meteorology, the theme for the year 2007: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Executive Council of the World Meteorological Organization (WMO) decided to set "Polar meteorology: understanding global impacts" as the theme for the year 2007. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent years witnessed global warming on the rise across the world due to the greenhouse gas emissions including the carbonic acid gas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the global warming has been observed more apparently in the poles with a great temperature disparity.  As a result, some of glacier and tundra have been melted away and the ice covering rivers and lakes reduced, thus causing a great danger to the eco-system in the areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Therefore, it is very important for each country to exert more efforts for the research into the polar meteorology, which has a great effect on the Earth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The case is the same with our country badly hit by the global warming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years, the temperature rise in our country is two or three times the average temperature rise on the globe in the 20th century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It compels the institute to intensify the research into the polar areas in the field of the climate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The institute plans to observe the El Nino effect on the polar areas.  It is also going to observe the relations between the El Nino and the meteorological conditions in the Polar zones and the relations between the meteorological conditions of the polar areas and the formation and development of high atmospheric pressure in the Sea of Okhotsk this year as the high atmospheric pressure formed in the Sea of Okhotsk brought cold to the east coast of Korea in recent years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through the media the state is working hard to help the people have a good understanding of the influence of the global warming, reduction of ice acreage in the Arctic Regions and the hole of the ozone layer on the earth.

Promising Women's Ice Hockey of DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- The women's ice hockey made a new start in the DPRK two decades ago with teenage girls who had a great ambition to glorify the nation's honor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first women's ice hockey team was organized in the then Jagang Provincial Sports Group in Juche 76 (1987), which was followed by various units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The women's ice hockey players had accumulated experience and courage through their continued playing tours. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK Women's Ice Hockey Team made its debut in the contest for the qualification for the World Women's Ice Hockey Championships (B Class) held in Hungary in March 2000 to win the first place. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is fully demonstrating its ability, overpowering the opponents with its intensive attack and tactful skating technique at the current 2007 World Women's Ice Hockey Championships (B Class). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun Yong Song, secretary of the DPRK Ice Hockey Association, told KCNA that the future of the DPRK women's ice hockey is optimistic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years the state investment in the women's ice hockey, he added, has been augmented and more similar teams have been organized in various sports groups. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Juvenile Sports School attached to the Ice Rink and other juvenile sports schools are training many talent reserves to dominate the world women's ice hockey.

Rodong Sinmun exhorta a acelerar la construccion de gran potencia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 23 de marzo (ATCC) -- El periodico Rodong Sinmun inserto en su numero del dia 23 un editorial dedicado al 90 aniversario de la fundacion de la Asociacion Nacional Coreana por el indoblegable combatiente revolucionario Kim Hyong Jik. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La fundacion de la ANC el 23 de marzo del 6 (1917) de la Era Juche fue un evento historico que dio lugar al viraje trascendental en el desarrollo del movimiento antijapones de liberacion nacional de Corea, senala el editorial y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La historia de la gran direccion iniciada con la idea de "Jiwon (gran proposito)" y proseguida fielmente de generacion en generacion hoy dia la lleva adelante consecutivamente el Dirigente Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Con el sublime sentido de mision asumida ante la epoca y la revolucion, la patria y el pueblo el Dirigente hace todos sus esfuerzos por coronar la causa revolucionaria del Juche iniciada en el monte Paektu. Gracias al Dirigente los coreanos pudieron ser el orgulloso pueblo revolucionario que vive y lucha de generacion en generacion con la idea de "Jiwon" de Kim Hyong Jik y sobre esta tierra se da inicio a una nueva historia de la construccion de la gran potencia prospera en que se realizan a plenitud el ideal y el anhelo de los precursores revolucionarios bajo la bandera del Songun (priorizacion militar). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La revolucion coreana conducida por el Dirigente es la del fuerte caracter Juche que materializa estrictamente el ideal de independencia nacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La bandera de independencia nacional enarbolada por Kim Hyong Jik en el camino matutino de la revolucion coreana flamea invariablemente hoy tambien bajo la guia del Dirigente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La revolucion coreana guiada por este es la prometedora que sale siempre victoriosa con el poderio de la camaraderia revolucionaria y de la unidad monolitica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Kim Hyong Jik creo la sublime historia de la camaraderia revolucionaria en el camino de la ardua lucha en que presento y materializo la idea de "Jiwon".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Es noble el origen de la tradicion de la camaraderia de la revolucion coreana y esta asegurada firmemente su continuacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La revolucion coreana conducida por el Dirigente es la invencible que logra victorias con el indoblegable espiritu de lucha. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Kim Hyong Jik enseno que el revolucionario debe estar dispuesto a morir de hambre, morir a mano ajena y morir de frio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El pueblo coreano es el heroico que lucha con la indoblegable conviccion infundida por el Dirigente. Con este espiritu convirtio la "marcha penosa" en una feliz y abrio un ancho camino de la construccion de la gran potencia prospera superando multiples dificultades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  De veras es la maxima gloria del pueblo coreano llevar adelante energicamente la revolucion y la construccion de generacion en generacion tomando riendas del baton de relevos de la revolucion y gozando de la fortuna de tener al gran lider y gran hombre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Debemos glorificar de generacion en generacion la historia de herencia de la revolucion coreana al apoyar con lealtad la politica de Songun del Dirigente y defender a costa de la vida la Direccion de la Revolucion.

Maniobras militares EE.UU.- Sur de Corea obstaculizan el logro de la paz
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 23 de marzo (ATCC) -- Si Estados Unidos y las autoridades surcoreanas desean el desenlace favorable de la corriente de reconciliacion dada en la Peninsula Coreana, tienen que abandonar incondicionalmente su intento de desplegar los imprudentes ejercicios militares conjuntos para agredir al Norte de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Senala asi el rotativo Rodong Sinmun en un articulo individual de este viernes y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Estas maniobras miliares, que EE.UU. y las fuerzas belicistas del Sur de Corea desarrollan cada ano en esta parte, devienen factor principal que amenaza la paz de la Peninsula Coreana y agrava la confrontacion y tension. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Sin pararlas, es imposible eliminar en esta area la confrontacion militar, la tension y el peligro de guerra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El "ejercicio combinado de refuerzo para el tiempo de guerra" y el simulacro "Aguilucho" son los mas tipicos para ejercitar la invasion al Norte de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Este ano, decenas de miles de uniformados estadounidenses arribaran al suelo surcoreano con el portaaviones de propulsion nuclear, los cazabombarderos Stealth y otros medios belicos sofisticados, que se hicieron "famosos" por sus efectos mortiferos en la guerra iraqui y las otras de agresion desatadas en varias regiones del mundo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Se considera que las maniobras de este ano resultaran mas provocativas que las anteriores ediciones porque dan importancia al entrenamiento de las operaciones ofensivas como el desembarco, el cruce del rio y el ataque a la profundidad de retaguardia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Si EE.UU. y los belicistas surcoreanos las llevan a cabo finalmente, manifestaran una vez mas su hostilidad e intento de invadir a la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El dialogo y el ejercicio militar son incompatibles.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Pues, los hechos aleccionadores del pasado confirman que ningun dialogo puede resultar fructifero en medio de las detonaciones de los ejercicios belicos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tales maniobras conjuntas ocasionaran consecuencias negativas como impedir la solucion pacifica del problema nuclear de la Peninsula Coreana, hacer volver a la coyuntura critica las relaciones Norte-Sur e fomentar el ambiente de confrontacion y guerra.

ANC, exploradora del camino de independencia y unidad nacionales
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 23 de marzo (ATCC) -- Hoy se cumple el 90 aniversario de la fundacion de la Asociacion Nacional Coreana (ANC) por Kim Hyong Jik, indoblegable combatiente revolucionario y destacado dirigente del movimiento antijapones de liberacion nacional de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@ En la decada de 1910, cuando el destino de la nacion coreana se hallaba en el dilema de vida o muerte por la ocupacion de Corea por los imperialistas japoneses, el movimiento antijapones del pueblo coreano estaba descuartizado y sufria sucesivos fracasos debido a las maniobras separatistas y el servilismo a las grandes potencias de los nacionalistas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Tras examinar profundamente esta realidad, Kim Hyong Jik aquilato que para acabar con la politica de represion fascista de los imperialistas japoneses y lograr la independencia nacional, era preciso apoyarse en las propias fuerzas nacionales y fundar una organizacion revolucionaria firme en la posicion independiente antiimperialista y bien arraigada en las masas populares e impulso con dinamismo los preparativos concernientes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Por fin, el organizo la ANC el 23 de marzo del 6 (1917) de la Era Juche en Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Esta entidad fue la mayor organizacion revolucionaria clandestina antijaponesa entre las constituidas en el pais y en el extranjero por los patriotas coreanos en el periodo circundante al Levantamiento Popular del Primero de Marzo y tuvo por su objetivo lograr la independencia nacional con las propias fuerzas de los coreanos unidos como un solo hombre y fundar un autentico Estado civilizado. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Con ella, el movimiento antijapones de liberacion nacional llego a contar por fin con la organizacion medular que aglutino a amplias masas populares con su correcta meta de lucha y se dio una nueva coyuntura que posibilito alcanzar la unidad de las fuerzas revolucionarias antijaponesas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Bajo la orientacion de Kim Hyong Jik, la ANC diversifico sus formas de lucha, incluyendo las actividades armadas revolucionarias, y llamo activamente a las masas populares a la lucha antijaponesa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En particular, contribuyo grandemente a lograr la transicion del proceso nacionalista a la revolucion proletaria en el movimiento referido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Las inmortales proezas, que el realizo en aras de la independencia y la unidad nacionales allanando el camino de la revolucion coreana, son heredadas y desarrolladas por el Presidente Kim Il Sung y se glorifican por el Dirigente Kim Jong Il quien encarna en el maximo nivel el ideal de amor a la patria, la nacion y el pueblo.
